s=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\"></span></span></span><span class=\"fix\"></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span>","key":"ViDVVV1ZcG"},{"type":"text","value":"):","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1},"end":{"line":47,"column":1}},"key":"jpet4iGe90"}],"key":"XZXq23iNCW"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":49,"column":1},"end":{"line":49,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If the null value, 0, falls outside the confidence interval, H~o~ is rejected.","position":{"start":{"line":49,"column":1},"end":{"line":49,"column":1}},"key":"a6AR2xHjiv"}],"key":"lqTWdwDfzJ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If the null value, 0, falls inside the confidence interval, H~o~ is not rejected.","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"key":"nbKZl09EaH"}],"key":"ug5FtAllV1"},{"type":"admonition","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Example","position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":53,"column":1}},"key":"wFH08KTGe3"}],"key":"UQPHhdkW6x"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"Let's go back to our twin study example, where we found a 95% confidence interval for\t$\\mu_{d}$ of (-6.11322, 0.30072) and a p-value of 0.074.\n\nWe used the fact that the p-value is .074 to conclude that H~o~ can not be rejected (at the .05 significance level), and that whether or not a person was raised by his or her birth parents doesn't necessarily have an effect on intelligence (as measured by IQ scores). The last comment tells us that we can also use the confidence interval to reach the same conclusion, since 0 falls inside the confidence interval for $\\mu_{d}$. In other words, since 0 is a plausible value for $\\mu_{d}$ we cannot reject H~o~ which claims that $\\mu_{d}=0$.","position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"key":"GzqFjHKQIE"}],"key":"oTGs8nbr4E"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":59,"column":1},"end":{"line":59,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Learn By Doing","position":{"start":{"line":59,"column":1},"end":{"line":59,"column":1}},"key":"SLa54Moknq"}],"identifier":"learn-by-doing","label":"Learn By Doing","html_id":"learn-by-doing","implicit":true,"key":"dnkAXPX5bI"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":61,"column":1},"end":{"line":61,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A publishing company wanted to test whether typing speed differs when using word processor A or word processor B. A random sample of 25 typists was selected and the typing speeds (in words per minute) were recorded for each secretary when using word processor A and then when using word processor B. (Which word processor was used first was determined for each typist by a coin flip).","position":{"start":{"line":61,"column":1},"end":{"line":61,"column":1}},"key":"S3nT6dtcw0"}],"key":"RJrPzGE1pg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":63,"column":1},"end":{"line":63,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Based on the collected data, a 95% confidence interval for μ~d~, the mean difference (word processor A - word processor B) was found to be (2.5, 7.8).","position":{"start":{"line":63,"column":1},"end":{"line":63,"column":1}},"key":"G2gNSLOFv1"}],"key":"pNHyN2W1X0"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":65,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The appropriate hypotheses for testing whether the typing speeds differ when using word processor A or word processor B is the two-sided test:","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":65,"column":1}},"key":"yEWqNSv8ai"}],"key":"Afs7G7K1RV"},{"type":"container","kind":"figure","children":[{"type":"image","url":"/build/image417-280ae31b9f9e6e27e94d91ffc5154de4.gif","alt":"H_0: μ_d = 0, H_a: μ_d ≠ 0","key":"T4vsRdMxtV","urlSource":"images/image417.gif"},{"type":"caption","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"H_0: μ_d = 0, H_a: μ_d ≠ 0","position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"key":"Z4p032MuSd"}],"key":"LYeCkaq0uU"}],"key":"lFTm7wtbCH"}],"enumerator":"1","key":"uezcQhO81u"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note","key":"uDOl8d8JKD"}],"key":"k4RolXruRl"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"**Sectionnest**\n\n*(Interactive activity — available in the OLI platform)*","position":{"start":{"line":74,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"key":"Gqe6fTXytv"}],"key":"i3Y24AbPHh"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note","key":"HvmZCfhLvR"}],"key":"aGEjX0Q2qS"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"**Sectionnest**\n\n*(Interactive activity — available in the OLI platform)*","position":{"start":{"line":80,"column":1},"end":{"line":82,"column":1}},"key":"UYt4fUeacu"}],"key":"aAJ9CNLRPH"}],"key":"zTGqgcfOqQ"}],"key":"tC0DveIr9m"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Matched Pairs (6 of 8)","url":"/pages/m16-matched-pairs-6-of-8","group":"Unit 5: Inference"},"next":{"title":"Matched Pairs (8 of 8)","url":"/pages/m16-matched-pairs-8-of-8","group":"Unit 5: Inference"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3001"}